id: pm-q1ke
title: "Bundle GH-433 self-parent guard, Windows nightly lock proof, and pnpm 11 bootstrap hardening"
description: "Implementation bundle for current live failures: reject parent self-cycles at mutation time, harden the Windows Node 24 lock coverage assertion behind GH-427, and migrate pnpm 11 build-script/override settings so local bootstrap and release gates run reliably."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: "area:lifecycle","area:release",pnpm,robustness,windows
created_at: "2026-07-05T10:35:05.590Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-05T14:30:07.466Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: "pm update --parent <same-id> rejects before writing; create/update parent self-cycle regression coverage passes; Windows lock coverage no longer depends on POSIX-only write-failure behavior; pnpm 11 bootstrap succeeds with reviewed allowBuilds/overrides in pnpm-workspace.yaml; focused tests, full coverage, static quality, temp-dir smoke, changelog check, and release-health evidence recorded."
parent: pm-98cz
resolution: Self-parent create/update mutations now reject before writes; explicit create ids are registered through the SDK command contract; pnpm 11 bootstrap configuration and CI examples are aligned; Windows lock coverage remains portable.
expected_result: pm create/update cannot persist a parent self-cycle; package authors can discover and use pm create --id through generated contracts/help; pnpm 11 installs use workspace-level allowBuilds/overrides; all gates and installed-package smoke pass.
actual_result: "Focused regressions passed, full coverage reached 100/100/100/100 across 264 files / 5423 tests, static/security/release gates passed, installed-package smoke passed, pm-changelog check remained clean, Greptile follow-up coverage was added for Windows lock and built-CLI update self-parent paths, and final bot findings were addressed with typed-value self-parent error detail, bounded dependency override ranges, and shared placeholder-token detection."
